Definition: become less tense, rest, or take one's ease
Example: He relaxed in the hot tub; Let's all relax after a hard day's work
Synonyms: adj, all, depressant, relaxant, noun, process, relaxation, act, tense, loosen_up, unbend, unwind, decompress, slow_down, verb, change, change_state, become, less, rest, or, take, one, s, ease, He, relaxed, in, the, hot, tub, Let, after, a, hard, day, work
